National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with President Catherine Samba-Panza of the Central African Republic to congratulate her and the country on the recent peaceful national elections and the upcoming end of the transitional period. Rice commended President Samba-Panza for her leadership and progress towards peace and reconciliation. They both emphasized the importance of an inclusive government that represents the diversity of the country. They also expressed concern over reports of sexual exploitation and abuse by UN peacekeeping forces and supported swift accountability and enforcement of a zero tolerance policy. Rice reiterated the United States' commitment to being a friend and partner to the Central African Republic.